3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep learning techniques to solve the problem of super-resolution, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with improving the quality of images, which is a common problem in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses peak signal to noise ratio (PSNR) and structural similarity (SSIM) as evaluation metrics, which are commonly used in information theory.
